OL,3,CVeterans given rent rises despite
OL,4,Cbeing unable to go home for 10 months
OL,6,FKeith Sunter from the charity says:
OL,7,F"Whatever they have needed we have
OL,8,Fhelped them with, through the
OL,9,FBailiff's Fund and our funding as
OL,10,Fwell."
OL,12,FThe Chief Operating Officer of Haig
OL,13,FHousing Trust, William Lindsay, has
OL,14,Fdefended the group's commitment to
OL,15,Fveterans.
OL,17,FHe says: "We have a roofer who is now
OL,18,Fworking on the properties which are
OL,19,Fnot habitable and we have always made
OL,20,Fthem a priority.
